# Medium

This class repressents the different forms in which Titles are available for sale.
There are curently two kinds of Meidum: Print medium and eBook medium, which are detailed
in their own classes. Audio books may be added at a later date. This class has no
state diagram because it is a superclass and the state models are unique to the 
subclasses.

◇

superclass_of_key: medium

attributes:
    isbin:
        name: "ISBN"
        index_nums: [0] # Index zero is "key"
        details: |
            The Internaltional Standard Book Nummber assigned by the Publisher to this Medium.
            ISBNs are unique by Medium; the eBook and Print medium versions of the same Title
            will have different ISBNs. More information on ISBNs can be found online.
        rules: either ISBN-10 or ISBN-13 format as dfined by www.isbn-international.org
    price:
        name: "selling price"
        details: |
            The current per-copy price that WebBooks is offering this Medium to customers. In some 
            cases, WebBooks may offer certain Media for free.
        rules: $0.00 .. unconstrained in US Dollars, to the nearest whole cent
    cost:
        name: "acquisition cost"
        details: |
            The price that WebBooks pays the Publisher for each copy of this Medium so that
            profit can be calculated. In some cases, publishers may give copies to WebBooks at no cost.
        rules: $0.00 .. unconstrained in US Dollars, to the nearest whole cent
    visible:
        name: "is visible"
        details: |
            Media may be visible or invisible. When visible, this Medium will appear to Customers
            in the catalog (e.g., when they do searches). When not visible, this Medium won't appear
            to Customers although it is still know to the business (Managers can still see it).
            This allows WebBooks to pre-stage Media before going live as well as take them down 
            when necessary (without deleting them).
        rules: true or false
